<section class="container section-stack">
  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <details>
    <summary>
      Do I always need a full service upgrade to add more capacity?
    </summary>
    <p>
      No. Sometimes the issue is panel space or organization rather than total
      service size. The right path depends on the loads you have now and what
      you plan to add next.
    </p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>
      Can a panel upgrade help with future remodel or charging plans?
    </summary>
    <p>
      Yes. Many upgrades are justified because they create cleaner capacity for
      a remodel, EV charger, backup power plan, or additional dedicated
      circuits.
    </p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>
      Will the panel be labeled clearly after the work is complete?
    </summary>
    <p>
      That is part of the value. Better organization and labeling make future
      service faster and reduce confusion for owners and technicians.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>

